The Deputy Majority Leader of the Nigerian Senate, Professor Robert Ajayi Boroffice, on Friday obtained the expression of interest and nomination form to contest for the office of the president under the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC). Boroffice is a ranking Senator, who was first elected as senator in 2011. He has won three successive senatorial elections in Ondo North Senatorial District and is the only Senator on the platform of APC from Ondo State. In 2019, Boroffice was a leading candidate for the office of the Deputy Senate Presidency, he eventually withdrew from the race, citing deference to the wish of President Muhammadu Buhari. Boroffice started his early career as University lecturer in University of Ibadan and Lagos State University (LASU). He has P.hD in Human Genetics and Post-Doctorate Research Fellowship from University of Newcastle, England.